    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-09-10T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-09-10T13:00:00-05:00" n="712"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d712">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">352.115/78: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Barcelona</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-10T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 10, 1936—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your undated telegram received September 6th relating to Cataluna decree of
                    prohibition on gold. Please inform first, whether the Catalan Government had
                    authority under Spanish Government to issue decree and whether it was regularly
                    issued in accordance with law, second whether it allows safety deposit boxes to
                    be opened without permission or presence of their owners, and third whether the
                    pesetas proposed to be given actually have the value at which they are reckoned.
                    We are making same inquiry of Madrid.<note n="23" xml:id="d712fn23">Telegram No.
                        115, September 10, 2 p.m., to the Third Secretary of Embassy in Spain, not
                        printed.</note> Defer protest pending instructions. You are, of course,
                    aware of our own legislation that requires delivery of all gold to Federal
                    Reserve Banks. It is possible that Catalan plan is of same nature and is,
                    therefore, not subject to objection by us.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
